column1: We love our dogs. They love to race.

column5: Owned/Raced by: Sparkle and Fade Syndicate
column7: Trained by: B D F Craik

column1: INDI SHAE (2) - checked outwards off heels exiting the bend before shifting ground inwards off heels shortly after entering the home straight.
GET ME HOME (4) - shouldered with CLEVER ESTER in the run to the bend. Checked from behind rounding the bend.
CLEVER ESTER (5) - shouldered with GET ME HOME in the run to the bend. Contacted from the inside by FERNANDO CHARM rounding the bend and raced wide.
FERNANDO CHARM (7) - slow early stages. Awkwardly placed on heels rounding the bend shifting outwards bumping with CLEVER ESTER.

column7: Trained by: J Udy & D Cottam

column1: LOUDRED (2) - awkwardly placed on heels entering the bend falling to the track as a consequence. Referred to the Veterinarian and cleared of injury.
CLEVER HARPER (5) - checked from behind entering the bend.
KAPAI CHRIS (6) - jostled with BOTANY SANDY in the run to the bend before being obligated to check off this runners heels. Hampered by fallen runner entering the bend.
MRS. OPAL (7) - began awkwardly settling a distant last.
BOTANY SANDY (8) - jostled with KAPAI CHRIS in the runto the bend.

BIGTIME HUNTER (1) - slow early. Lost ground with the field rounding the bend. Referred to the Veteriantrain where is was reported to have have general soreness to its right sartorius, hip support and quadricep muscles. Stewards questioned the racing programme of this greyhound with co-rainer R O'Regan who explained he would consult with the connections in the coming days as to the racing future of the greyhound and report the decision to Stewards.
FORD MAN (3) - clipped heels prior to the finish line.
KAI NAN (4) - obligated to check inwards in the run to the bend losing momentum.
OUR GREG (5) - squeezed for racing room early stages.
BOTANY THOMMO (8) - clipped from behind prior to the finish line.

column7: Trained by: J Udy & D Cottam

column1: RAINY RIVER (1) - jostled with BIGTIME GAL in the run to the bend.
BIGTIME GAL (2) - squeezed for racing room in the run to the bend jostling with RAINY RIVER as a consequence. Awkwardly placed on heels entering the bend and shifted up the track losing ground.
GAIN CAPITAL (3) - bumped with BIGTIME GAL on several occasions in the run to the bend.
GREY WAY (4) - hampered in the run to the bend.
NOISE MAKER (5) - bumped with GREY WAY in the run to the bend.
CRACKLING GAL (4) - obliged to steady early stages when placed on heels.
BEAR CLAWS (5) - raced wide first turn and through the back straight.
LIONEL KEEPING (6) - faltered in its gait first turn. Continued to gallop awkwardly there after losing ground. Referred to the Veteraitian where it was reported to have a torn right triceps muscle.

column3: Jo's Wholesale & Sports Bar Taipa Tavern Sprint

column7: Trained by: J Udy & D Cottam

column1: BLOCKER (3) - collided with MADAM BUCKS on jumping. Bumped down the track prior to the bend losing ground.
MADAM BUCKS (4) - collided with BLOCKER on jumping. Placed in tight quarters prior to the bend having to check inwards and lose momentum as a consequence.

ON DA QUEST (8) - faltered entering the bend losing ground. Continued to lose ground thereafter. Referred to the Veterinarian where it was reported to have a torn left gracilis, pain in right hock and left triceps.
HANDS OF STEEL (10/5) - lost momentum when awkwardly laced on heels entering the bend.
AGBEZE (4) - hind quarters brushed by TRIBAL CONQUEST prior to the bend. Awkwardly placed on heels entering the bend having to check and hamper trailing runners.
MAGIC EIGHT BALL (5) - slow early. Obligated to race wide rounding the bend.
TRIBAL CONQUEST (7) - checked inwards off heels in the run to the bend. Brushed the hind quarters of AGBEZE prior to the bend. Checked and lost ground entering the bend.
ALWAYS DREAMING (3) - bumped down the track and into restricted room early stages losing ground. Checked in off heels entering the bend.
ASSERTING POWER (4) - contacted from the outside early stages. Hampered and had to check entering the bend.
BOTANY RIFLES (5) - hampered early stages having to check outwards off heels.
OPAWA LOLA (7) - bumped up the track rounding the bend.
SMASH OUT (8) - awkwardly placed to the outside of runners entering the bend losing ground.
TILLY'S SILLY (9/6) - shifted down the track early stages impeding inside runners. Lost momentum when in restricted room entering the bend.
HI HO TONTO (1) - slow early stages. Checked by fallen runner entering the bend.

OUT OF PAPER (2) - jostled with MY SNUGGLES in the run to the bend losing ground. Obligated to check off the heels of KAPAI STEWIE prior to the bend. Placed in tight quarters entering the bend losing ground before being terminally dragged down and falling to the track. Referred to the Veterinarian and cleared of injury
SMASH BURTON (3) - slow early stages. Climbed on the heels of OUT OF PAPER entering the bend losing its chance. Referred to the Veterinarian and cleared of injury.
MY SNUGGLES (4) - jostled with OUT OF PAPER in the run to the bend.
ZUGZWANG (1) - slow to jump. Hind quarters brushed briefly entering the bend.
TRES VITE (2) - contacted from the outside in the run to the bend.

BIGTIME ZACK (3) - slow to jump. Became awkward in its gait entering the bend after brushing the hind quarters of ZUGZWANG losing ground. Referred to the Veterinarian where it was reported to have a torn right hip support.
BIGTIME THOR (4) - forced down the track and into restricted room in the run to the bend.
SNOOPY'S HERO (5) - came down the track in the run to the bend hampering inside greyhounds. Squeezed for racing room entering the bend losing ground.
HEART SHAPED BOX (1) - hampered early stages. Referred to the Veterinarian after appearing lame exiting the track where it was reported to be lame in its right hip on extension.
ROD'S GIRL (2) - hampered early stages.Squeezed for racing room entering the first bend.
SEFTON STAN (3) - hampered early stages. Squeezed for racing room entering the first bend
JINJA NICE (4) - shifted down the track early stages hampering inside greyhounds.
DIG DIG DIG (6) - checked from behind entering the first turn. Awkwardly placed on heels rounding the first bend having to check.
MONSOON MALABAR (8) - bumped from the inside first bend.
OPAWA DELIGHT (9/5) - checked off heels and ran wide first bend.

column5: Owned/Raced by: Pave The Way Syndicate

column1: LOOKING SNATCHED (3) - collided with outside runner early stages.
FROSTY BLAZE (6) - squeezed for racing room early stages losing ground.
COSMIC METEOR (7) - squeezed for racing room early stages losing ground.

BIGTIME HEARTY (8) - placed inside runners in some difficulty when shifting down the track in the run to the bend. Raced up the track rounding the bend losing ground before becoming awkwardly placed on heels. Referred to the Veterinarian where it was reported to be lame in its right wrist.
